Germany May Pay 35 Billion Euros for Euro Rescue, Die Welt Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-03-27T12:17:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/germany-may-pay-35-billion-euros-for-euro-rescue-die-welt-says.html
Germany  may have to pay as much as
35 billion euros ($49 billion) in the coming years to bail out
some European countries via the future euro emergency aid
mechanism and existing rescue funds,  Welt am Sonntag  reported
today, citing a survey by the DIW economic research institute.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 